## 1.8.3
- Added shared frontend error normalization utility with tests and removed `any`-based catch handling in key routes.
- Hardened process instance and document type pages with explicit loading/error/empty states and safer date/message rendering.
- Typed document type designer schema handling using `ProcessFieldLibrary` with guarded JSON parsing.
- Made Sentry source-map upload conditional to eliminate noisy build warnings without credentials.
- Added browser console smoke check tooling (`npm run test:browser-console`) and optional verification toggle (`BPM_FRONTEND_ENABLE_BROWSER_SMOKE`).
- Extended automation smoke tests and Makefile targets to cover new browser-smoke controls.

## 1.8.2
- Tightened frontend API typing by replacing `any`-based document/task/notification contracts with shared interfaces.
- Improved process documentation page reliability with explicit BPMN viewer/registry typing and component cleanup on unmount.
- Updated release metadata and usage documentation to align with the 1.8.2 patch release.

## 1.8.1
- Added JSON/Markdown summary aggregate status and totals metadata.
- Added report artifact retention pruning via `BPM_RUNNER_ARTIFACT_RETENTION_DAYS`.
- Hardened retry helper validation and expanded automation smoke tests for schema and retention checks.
